dcterms:description: The Free Spoken Digit Dataset (FSDD) consists of voice recordings of spoken digits from 0 to 9 by six speakers. For this study, only the recordings of one speaker named 'Jackson' were used, with 50 spoken digit recordings for each class, sampled at 8 kHz.
dcterms:title: Free Spoken Digit Dataset (FSDD)

dcterms:description: The Concentric Circle Data (CCD) is a synthetic dataset used for binary classification tasks, consisting of two concentric circles that can be either overlapping or non-overlapping.
dcterms:title: Concentric Circle Data (CCD)

dcterms:description: The Overlapping Concentric Circle Data (OCCD) is a synthetic dataset used for binary classification tasks, consisting of two overlapping concentric circles.
dcterms:title: Overlapping Concentric Circle Data (OCCD)

dcterms:description: The Prey-Predator dataset is a hypothetical dataset used for binary classification tasks, where the goal is to classify stimuli as either prey or predator based on their size.
dcterms:title: Prey-Predator dataset
